|WKO=====================================================================
 |CKBStatus Effects: Buffs and Debuffs
|WKO=====================================================================
|YKOMost temporary conditions on your character are effects. Helpful
effects are buffs; harmful ones are debuffs. The |YKBbuffs|YKO command
lists both, numbered, with the time each has left.

Buffs come from guild abilities, potions, equipment, implants, and
special events. Timed buffs count down in real time. Buffs supplied by
an item you are using last as long as the item does and are shown as
"Permanent". You can end your own buffs early with |YKBclearbuff|YKO.

Debuffs are poisons, diseases, hexes, and similar afflictions. Most
deal damage every few seconds until they expire. Landing the same
affliction again either refreshes its timer or simply fails while the
first still runs - debuffs do not stack into stronger versions of
themselves. |YKBclearbuff|YKO cannot remove them; they end on their own
or through the right cure or dispel.

Bodily conditions are a special family of debuff: Burning, Bleeding,
Chilled, Freezing, and Exposed. Burning and Bleeding grow in strength
when fed by further attacks - |YKBbuffs|YKO shows the current strength
as a number - up to a cap that scales with your level. Being chilled
again while already chilled deepens into Freezing, and Exposed leaves
your defenses open to attack. These conditions fade with time, and
some also yield to the world itself: a warm hearth will thaw a deep
chill.

Not every ability registers with this display, so |YKBbuffs|YKO may not
show everything acting on you.

